         <div type="translation">
            <ab>(Recto);;Artemidoros, barber, to Zenon(?) greeting. [As] you wrote, I gave to Artemidoros, the son of Sochares and to [- - -] the price of a barber's iron tool, nine drachmai. In order that you know, [- - -] according to the slave [- - -] in order that he can attend us.;Farewell. Year 37, Apellaios 17, Choiak 21.;;(Verso);Year 37, Choiak 21. From Artemidoros, barber, to Zenon . . . of iron, 9 drachmai.</ab>
         </div>
